    examples.append({
        "instruction": "You are the supply chain AI for MediCare Pharmaceuticals India. Analyze this export opportunity.",
        "input": "WHO prequalification opens ₹500 crore export opportunity for our antiretroviral (HIV) drugs to Sub-Saharan Africa. Requires WHO-GMP certification. Current status: Only CDSCO certified. Certification timeline: 18-24 months. Investment required: ₹8 crore.",
        "output": "WHO PREQUALIFICATION - AFRICA EXPORT OPPORTUNITY\n\nOPPORTUNITY ANALYSIS:\n- Market: Sub-Saharan Africa HIV treatment market\n- Revenue potential: ₹500 crore over 5 years (₹100 crore/year)\n- Products: Antiretrovirals (ARVs) - Tenofovir, Efavirenz, Lamivudine\n- Access via: Global Fund, PEPFAR, UNICEF tenders\n- Requirement: WHO Prequalification of medicines program (PQ)\n- Indian precedent: Cipla, Dr. Reddy's, Aurobindo already WHO-PQ certified\n\nCURRENT GAP ASSESSMENT:\n- CDSCO certified: Meets Indian standards only\n- WHO-GMP: More stringent (documentation, validation, quality systems)\n- Gap areas:\n  1. Quality Management System (QMS) documentation\n  2. Validated analytical methods\n  3. Stability data (ICH guidelines)\n  4. Technical dossier preparation\n  5. Site master file (SMF)\n\nCERTIFICATION PATHWAY:\n\nPHASE 1 (Month 1-6): Gap Analysis & Remediation\n- Hire WHO-GMP consultant: ₹1.5 crore\n- Internal audit against WHO standards\n- Identify and fix all gaps\n- Major areas: SOP documentation, training records, equipment validation\n\nPHASE 2 (Month 7-12): Dossier Preparation\n- Technical dossier per CTD (Common Technical Document) format\n- Bioequivalence studies: ₹2 crore (required for WHO-PQ)\n- Stability studies: 12-month accelerated + ongoing real-time\n- Laboratory: Upgrade to WHO-compliant analytical equipment\n- Investment: ₹3 crore\n\nPHASE 3 (Month 13-18): WHO Application\n- Submit dossier to WHO Product Assessment team\n- WHO inspection: They visit facility\n- Response to deficiency letters (multiple rounds typical)\n- Timeline: 12-18 months from submission\n\nPHASE 4 (Month 19-24): Approval & Commercial Launch\n- WHO PQ granted\n- Register products in target countries (Uganda, Kenya, Tanzania)\n- Global Fund tender participation\n- First revenues: Month 25+\n\nINVESTMENT BREAKDOWN:\n- GMP consulting: ₹1.5 crore\n- Lab upgrades: ₹2 crore\n- Bioequivalence studies: ₹2 crore\n- Regulatory dossier preparation: ₹1 crore\n- Staff training: ₹50 lakh\n- Contingency: ₹1 crore\n- Total: ₹8 crore\n\nFINANCIAL PROJECTION:\n- Investment: ₹8 crore over 24 months\n- Year 3 revenue: ₹80 crore\n- Year 4 revenue: ₹120 crore\n- Year 5 revenue: ₹150 crore\n- 5-year revenue: ₹420 crore\n- 5-year net margin (15%): ₹63 crore\n- ROI: 7.9x (₹8 crore → ₹63 crore)\n\nRISKS:\n- WHO inspection fails: Delay of 12+ months\n  Mitigation: Pre-inspection by certified consultants\n- Competition: Cipla already established\n  Mitigation: Differentiate on price and service\n- Africa market volatility: Currency, political risk\n  Mitigation: Diversify across 10 countries\n- Global Fund pricing pressure: Thin margins\n  Mitigation: Volume compensates (100 crore revenue at 15% margin)\n\nSTRATEGIC VALUE:\n- WHO-PQ opens 100+ countries beyond Africa\n- Brand credibility: \"WHO approved\" enhances domestic standing too\n- Talent: Attracts quality professionals\n- Foundation: For future regulated market entry (US, EU)\n\nUrgency: MEDIUM - Long-term investment, start process within 3 months for 2-year payoff"
    })

