    examples.append({
        "instruction": "You are the supply chain AI for MediCare Pharmaceuticals India. Analyze this capital investment decision.",
        "input": "Current warehouse at 95% capacity. Business growing 20% annually. Options: (A) Expand current facility (+50% capacity, ₹15 crore, 12 months), (B) New dedicated cold chain facility in Mangalore (₹35 crore, 18 months), (C) 3PL outsourcing (₹5 crore setup, ₹8 crore/year ongoing). Business needs space in 6 months.",
        "output": "WAREHOUSE CAPACITY EXPANSION - INVESTMENT DECISION ANALYSIS\n\nCURRENT SITUATION:\n- Utilization: 95% (critically full)\n- Growth: 20%/year\n- Capacity needed in: 6 months\n- If no action in 6 months: Cannot accept new stock → miss growth → revenue loss\n\nOPTIONS ANALYSIS:\n\nOPTION A: EXPAND CURRENT FACILITY\n- Capacity: +50%\n- Cost: ₹15 crore\n- Timeline: 12 months\n- PROBLEM: Need capacity in 6 months; this takes 12\n- Verdict: Does not solve immediate problem\n- Unless: Phase 1 (temporary solutions in 6 months) + expand in 12\n\nOPTION B: NEW MANGALORE FACILITY\n- Capacity: Dedicated cold chain\n- Cost: ₹35 crore\n- Timeline: 18 months\n- PROBLEM: Neither solves immediate 6-month need\n- But: Strategic for cold chain biologics expansion\n- Verdict: Long-term correct, wrong timing for immediate crisis\n\nOPTION C: 3PL OUTSOURCING\n- Setup: ₹5 crore\n- Ongoing: ₹8 crore/year\n- Timeline: 3 months to activate (FASTEST)\n- Solves: 6-month crisis\n- Cost over 5 years: ₹5 crore + ₹40 crore = ₹45 crore\n- Comparison: Option A ₹15 crore owned (better long-term)\n- Verdict: Best for immediate solution, expensive long-term\n\nRECOMMENDED STRATEGY: HYBRID PHASED APPROACH\n\nPHASE 1 (Month 0-6): Emergency 3PL for overflow\n- Use 3PL for: Dry products (room temperature) overflow\n- Our current warehouse: Reserve for cold chain (highest value)\n- 3PL cost: ₹2 crore for 6 months (partial use)\n- Capacity problem: SOLVED immediately\n\nPHASE 2 (Month 6-18): Expand current facility\n- Begin: Option A expansion in parallel\n- Cost: ₹15 crore\n- Complete: Month 18\n- Transition: Back from 3PL to owned space as expansion completes\n\nPHASE 3 (Month 12-36): Evaluate Mangalore\n- If biologics expansion proceeds (as recommended in other scenarios)\n- Mangalore becomes: Dedicated cold chain hub for coastal India\n- Decision: Based on biologics business growth by month 12\n- Option B: Start construction if biologics business confirmed\n\nFINANCIAL COMPARISON:\n\nOption A only:\n- Immediate problem: Unsolved (12-month gap = ₹100 crore lost growth)\n- Long-term cost: ₹15 crore\n\nOption B only:\n- Immediate: Unsolved (18-month gap)\n- Long-term: ₹35 crore (strategic for cold chain)\n\nOption C only:\n- Immediate: Solved\n- 5-year total: ₹45 crore (expensive for owned-equivalent capacity)\n\nHybrid (Recommended):\n- Immediate: SOLVED (Phase 1 3PL)\n- 5-year total: ₹2 crore (3PL) + ₹15 crore (expansion) = ₹17 crore\n- Savings vs C alone: ₹28 crore over 5 years\n- Strategic: Option B decision deferred pending biologics strategy confirmation\n\nWAREHOUSE OPTIMIZATION (While expanding):\n- Vertical racking: Better cube utilization (increase by 20% at zero cost)\n- SKU rationalization: Remove slow movers (free 5% space)\n- Immediate: Creates 3-6 months breathing room\n- Cost: ₹25 lakh for racking upgrade\n\nKEY METRICS TO MONITOR:\n- Capacity utilization target: 75-80% (not 95%)\n- Trigger for next expansion: At 70% utilization, begin planning\n- 20% growth: Need 20% more space each year → plan 2 years ahead\n\nUrgency: CRITICAL - 3PL activation must begin immediately (3-month lead time)"
    })

